# Goal
Spectral counts are normalized as `log2(count + 1)` for the correlation
analysis. Bins for the alluvial are computed on the **raw** mean count per
protein × cell line × condition (across the four replicates):
| Bin     | Mean raw count (per condition)   |
|---------|----------------------------------|
| Na      | < 1   (essentially undetected)   |
| Low     | 1 – 19                           |
| Med     | 20 - 50                          |
| High    | ≥ 50                             |

