Same bin scheme (`Na`, `Low`, `Med`, `High` at thresholds 1 / 5 / 15 raw mean
counts), now applied to every protein in the dataset rather than only the
designed TFs. Expect the dominant flow to be Na → Na (most proteins are not
detected in any condition) and a large blue (lost) component going from
NE → Na in C1: this is the catTFRE selectivity — non-DNA-binding proteins
